                <span class=3D"u-content">
                    <h2 id=3D"what-are-the-different-life-stages-for-cats?&=
amp;nbsp;"><strong>What are the different life stages for cats?</strong>&nb=
sp;</h2><p>Cats live on average for around 12-14 years, and it=E2=80=99s no=
t unusual for some to reach their late teens or early twenties. So, what ar=
e the six life stages they pass through?&nbsp;</p><h3 id=3D"kitten:-0---6-m=
onths&amp;nbsp;">Kitten: 0 - 6 months&nbsp;</h3><p>During this stage, your =
cat will be growing quickly and learning about the world around them. Socia=
lisation is important to help them grow into confident adult cats.&nbsp;</p=
><h3 id=3D"junior:-7-months---2-years&amp;nbsp;">Junior: 7 months - 2 years=
&nbsp;</h3><p>The junior stage is like teens/young adults in people. By thi=
s point, your cat will have reached full size and developed survival instin=
cts.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><h3 id=3D"adult:-3-=E2=80=93-6-years&amp;nbsp;">Adult: =
3 =E2=80=93 6 years&nbsp;</h3><p>By the adult stage, your cat is mature phy=
sically and behaviourally. Regular exercise and mental stimulation are impo=
rtant for their physical and mental wellbeing.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><h3 id=3D"mat=
ure:-7-=E2=80=93-10-years&amp;nbsp;">Mature: 7 =E2=80=93 10 years&nbsp;</h3=
><p>Mature cats are equivalent to humans in their mid-40s to mid-50s and te=
nd to be less active than adult cats.&nbsp;</p><h3 id=3D"senior:-11-=E2=80=
=93-14-years&amp;nbsp;">Senior: 11 =E2=80=93 14 years&nbsp;</h3><p>By the s=
enior stage, your cat is likely to be less active. They may need help acces=
sing things around the home, for example, a litter tray with lower sides so=
 they can get in and out easily, and ramps to get to favourite sleeping are=
as if they=E2=80=99re unable to jump.&nbsp;</p><h3 id=3D"super-senior:-15-y=
ears+&amp;nbsp;">Super Senior: 15 years+&nbsp;</h3><p>Many cats reach this =
stage, and some won=E2=80=99t show any signs of being so senior in age. It=
=E2=80=99s important to keep a close eye on their behaviour to spot any sub=
tle changes that may indicate something=E2=80=99s not quite right.&nbsp;&nb=
sp;</p>
                </span>
