r-my-cat?&amp;nbsp;">How do I find out the equivalent human age for my cat?=
&nbsp;</h2><p>Working out your cat=E2=80=99s age in human years is simple:<=
strong> </strong>the first two years of a cat=E2=80=99s life equate to 24 h=
uman years and every year thereafter is equivalent to 4 human years.&nbsp;<=
/p><p>The table below shows the six life stages, ages, and equivalent human=
 age:&nbsp;</p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan=3D"1" colspan=3D"1"><p><strong=
>Life stage</strong>&nbsp;</p></td><td rowspan=3D"1" colspan=3D"1"><p><stro=
